item.title: Which printer is better?
item.dc:creator: @Lin Lin
item.description:
@Lin wrote:

I’d say the last one. The 3rd one seems just like the others but more expensive. In all my luck with printers, with every single printer, they always break and it’s probably because it was cheap. If you don’t want to end up literally smashing yours to bits (mainly for fun) with a hammer, then I’d recommend buying one that works for a long time.
